This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with learning representations for text applications. It also involves the use of spectral methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised learning techniques to supplement supervised learning, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper presents empirical results on two specific tasks, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
